<emphasis id="B940EABEFFF5FFE0D28561F10C040C06" box="[151,373,507,531]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Xyleborus granulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B5DFFF5FFE0D36961F10F410C06" author="Schedl, K. E." box="[379,560,506,531]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" pagination="337 - 399" refId="ref6516" refString="Schedl, K. E. (1975) New Scolytidae and Platypodidae from Papua and New Guinea IV. Annalen des Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien, 79, 337 - 399." type="journal article" year="1975">Schedl 1975: 366</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B36ACFFF5FFE0D285623609180D1C" blockId="7.[151,1437,571,886]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="B940EABEFFF5FFE0D28562360C650C43" bold="true" box="[151,276,572,598]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Taxonomy</emphasis>
. The 
<typeStatus id="548F880EFFF5FFE0D34662310CC70C40" box="[340,438,571,597]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">holotype</typeStatus>
(NMW) has been examined by RAB. The species was synonymised with 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D2FFFF5FFE0D6E662310DB60C6C" authority="(Browne 1974)" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="partitus">
<emphasis id="B940EABEFFF5FFE0D6E662310DB60C6C" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Xyleborus partitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B5DFFF5FFE0D2E262550CE10C6F" author="Schedl, K. E." box="[240,400,607,634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" pagination="117 - 124" refId="ref6549" refString="Schedl, K. E. (1980) Zur Synonymie der Borkenkafer. XXVIII. Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Osterreichischer Entomologen, 31 (1979), 117 - 124." type="journal article" year="1980">Schedl (1980)</bibRefCitation>
, but restored as a distinct species by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B5DFFF5FFE0D13B626A0EBC0C6F" author="Beaver, R. A." box="[809,973,608,634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" pagination="87 - 97" refId="ref5359" refString="Beaver, R. A. (1991) New synonymy and taxonomic changes in Pacific Scolytidae (Coleoptera). Annalen des Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien, 92 B, 87 - 97." type="journal article" year="1991">Beaver (1991)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B5DFFF5FFE0D1C56255098D0C6F" author="Hulcr, J. &amp; Cognato, A. I." box="[983,1276,607,634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" refId="ref6101" refString="Hulcr, J. &amp; Cognato, A. I. (2013) Xyleborini of New Guinea, a taxonomic monograph (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Thomas Say Publications in Entomology, Entomological Society of America, Annapolis, Maryland, 172 pp." type="book" year="2013">Hulcr and Cognato (2013)</bibRefCitation>
diagnosed the species, recognised that it could not be included in 
<emphasis id="B940EABEFFF5FFE0D0C162890ED90C88" box="[723,936,643,669]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">
<taxonomicName id="4C344D2FFFF5FFE0D0C162890E340C88" authorityName="Eichhoff" authorityYear="1864" box="[723,837,643,669]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" species="sens">Xyleborus</taxonomicName>
sens. str
</emphasis>
., and included it under ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D2FFFF5FFE0D6A6628908440C88" authorityName="Le Conte" authorityYear="1876" box="[1204,1333,643,669]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Xyleborini">Xyleborini</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B940EABEFFF5FFE0D752628E0DBE0CD4" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">incertae sedis</emphasis>
’. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA54B5DFFF5FFE0D2FA62A20CAA0CD7" author="Cognato, A. I. &amp; Smith, S. M. &amp; Beaver, R. A." box="[232,475,679,706]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" pagination="540 - 554" refId="ref5835" refString="Cognato, A. I., Smith, S. M. &amp; Beaver, R. A. (2020) Two new genera of Oriental xyleborine ambrosia beetles (Coleoptera, Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Zootaxa, 4722 (6), 540 - 554. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4722.6.2" type="journal article" year="2020">
Cognato 
<emphasis id="B940EABEFFF5FFE0D35D62A20CF90CD4" box="[335,392,679,705]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
in their phylogeny of 181 xyleborine species, showed that it lay on a branch distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D2FFFF5FFE0D2C762C10C360CF0" authorityName="Eichhoff" authorityYear="1864" box="[213,327,715,741]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EABEFFF5FFE0D2C762C10C360CF0" box="[213,327,715,741]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Xyleborus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species is distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D2FFFF5FFE0D19F62C109680CF0" authorityName="Beaver &amp; Petrov" authorityYear="2021" box="[909,1049,715,741]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Melanesicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940EABEFFF5FFE0D19F62C109680CF0" box="[909,1049,715,741]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Melanesicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
apart from 
<taxonomicName id="4C344D2FFFF5FFE0D68C62C608390CF0" authorityName="Beaver &amp; Petrov &amp; Sittichaya" authorityYear="2021" box="[1182,1352,715,741]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Melanesicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nukuruanus">
<emphasis id="B940EABEFFF5FFE0D68C62C608390CF0" box="[1182,1352,715,741]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">M. nukuruanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the lack of distinct striae, and the irregular arrangement of granules on the elytral declivity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32E6527FFF5FFE0D2D563190E530D38" box="[199,802,787,814]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8B36ACFFF5FFE0D2D563190E530D38" blockId="7.[151,1437,571,886]" box="[199,802,787,814]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis id="B940EABEFFF5FFE0D2D563190C280D38" bold="true" box="[199,345,787,813]" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Distribution</emphasis>
. The species is endemic to New 
<collectingCountry id="F323763CFFF5FFE0D0D863190E6E0D38" box="[714,799,787,813]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="7" pageNumber="170">Guinea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
